{
  "text": "Next, one proceeds as in (A21)\u00f7(A.26) of [CITATION_1] , withW i := W vi,s+si replacing W i , \u03b1 2 replacing \u03b1, E i := f i W i replacing i , in order to prove (25). Finally, (26) follows by the same telescopic argument as in 27 [CITATION_2] , except for taking into account, as done above, the double scale (69) of the \u03b1 i 's. ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "59519584",
    "[CITATION_2]": "59519584"
